      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DIVA'S DELIGHT (1) had the drop on the lead and went on to be beaten 5.5 lengths into third (23.11) at The Gardens in a NG over 400m. Form from her last run is proving to be solid. Overdue and is among the main hopes. BOLD CHARM (3) struggled in tougher grade last start after settling off pace at this track, but prior to that won by 2 lengths at Maitland (22.56) beating Red Ball Rocket in a Mix 3/4 on March 16. Comes through a solid form race last start. Key runner who gets her chance to atone. GREAT FLASH (7) has been below best and missed the frame last couple, finishing 5th (23.19) last time in a NG at The Gardens. Has won here at this journey. Solid formlines coming through his last run. Must be included in calculations. MY LITTLE MAGIC (8) is worth consideration after filling a hole at big odds last start.",
